{{zh-forms|alt=𢑚,𦥔,伸-“to extend; to stretch; to state; to explain”,𤰶,𠭙,𦦀,𠭜}}

===Glyph origin===
{{Han etyl}}

{{liushu|p}} — a bolt of lightning. Original character of {{och-l|電|lightning}} and {{och-l|神|god; deity; spirit}}.

===Etymology===
; “to extend; to state; to request; to announce; again”
: From {{och-l|引|to pull; to draw}} + devoicing causative or iterative ({{zh-ref|Schuessler, 2007}}).

; 9th earthly branch
: From sense "to extend", denoting the moon's "extending" phase, i.e. waxing half-moon with a concave edge ({{zh-ref|Smith, 2010}}).
: For its association with the monkey, compare {{cog|tai-pro|*liːŋᴬ||monkey}}, {{cog|hmn-pro|*ʔlinᴬ||monkey}}, and {{cog|hmx-mie-pro|*ʔbiŋᴬ||monkey}}.

; “Shanghai”
: From {{zh-l|春申江}}, an alternative name of {{zh-l|黃浦江}}, the largest river in Shanghai.

